artist_bios: Born in a coastal city in Ecuador, Ricky Cohete mainly grew up in Miami. He was inspired to explore photography due to mesmerizing Florida's lights.
Silvana Soriano is a Brazilian artist who considers narrative as the main idea in her work. Line and gesture also play an important role.
John Van Alstine is an American contemporary artist known for his sculptures made of stone and metal, usually granite or slate, and found object steel.
Jimmy Nelson, born in Sevenoaks, Kent, in 1967, is a British photojournalist and photographer known for his portraits of tribal and indigenous peoples.
Aurora Molina is a Cuban fiber artist whose recent work has become more political because of the hyper politicization of our environment today.
Believing the simplicity is the ultimate sophistication, Randal Ford is an American photographer best known for his studio portraits of animals.
Andrew Warhola, better known as Andy Warhol, was one of the most significant American artists and a central figure in the Pop Art movement.
Hunter & Gatti is a creative duo consisting of Cristian Borillo and Martin Cespedes, known for their innovative outlook on art, film, and photography.
Franck de las Mercedes is a Nicaraguan/American artist influenced by abstract expressionism, rock carvings, neo-expressionism, and Nicaraguan primitivism.
Columbian photographer Javier Ray creates works that explore the sensuality of the male body and the repeated elements of urban cities.
Eric Dever initially used a limited color palette and tight grids, later introducing the entire color spectrum and loose shapes into his work.
Heavily influenced by painting and considering cameras as his paintbrushes, Kyriakos Kaziras is a Greek photographer known for his pictorial approach.
Thomas Ruff is a German artist internationally acclaimed for his explorations of photography in serial works, portraits, and, most recently, digital images.
Andrea Bonfils is an American artist whose practice includes mixed media, photography, and encaustics and is driven by a desire to evoke sensation.
Naomi White is an American abolitionist feminist, artist, and educator, working on ideas at the intersection of political ecology and photography.
One of the most known artists of the 20th century, Pablo Picasso marked the artistic history with his prolific pieces varying in style and technique.
Leslie Sheryll is an American artist who explores female identity in a male-centric society, often incorporating nineteenth-century history and symbolism.
Known for their romantic and stylish photographs, Formento & Formento explore love, loss, uncanny and perverse, longing, and the burden of memory.
Mel Ramos was an American Pop artist most famous for his comic-book and pin-up style images and sculptures of naked, voluptuous females.
An American abstract artist, Ann Purcell works within tensions of paradox, ambiguity, duality and contradiction, while focusing on the working process.
A Spanish artist of great critical acclaim, Joan Miro was one of the key representatives of Surrealism that refused to identify himself as such.
Raised as a first-generation Greek/American, Christos J. Palios is a photographer whose personal perspectives were forger by two distinct cultures.
Salvador Dali was a Spanish Surrealist painter, one of the most famous, interesting, eccentric and talked-about personalities in the art history.
Caroline Christie is a Scottish-born contemporary painter and photographer, best known for her photographs of wild horses.
Roy Ahlgren was an American abstract artist whose compositions were unique with many being mathematically constructed with considerable precision.
Khotan Fernandez is a Mexican contemporary artist working in several disciplines – painting, drawing, sculpture, and installation.
Dan Christensen was an American abstract painter associated with Color Field painting, Lyrical Abstraction and Abstract Expressionism.
Josef Albers was a German painter and color theorist, known for Homage to the Square, a series of paintings exploring the artistic language of colors.
Tyler Shields is a Los Angeles-based photographer, film director and writer best known for his provocative images of Hollywood celebrities.
David Yarrow is a British photographer, an ex-businessman, now famous for his black and white images of endangered animals and remote landscapes.
Manuel Santelices is a Chilean artist and journalist who explores the worlds of fashion, society and pop culture. He lives and works in New York.
Walter Darby Bannard was an American abstract painter, notable curator and writer on art.
David Shrigley is a Glasgow-based British artist best known for his illustrations that make satirical comments on mundane situations.
Guilherme Licurgo is a Brazilian photographer. He was invited to model for Terry Richardson for his book "Terry Richardson Rio Cidade Maravilhosa" in 2008.
Miguel Winograd is a Colombian photographer whose work explores the relationship between people and their environment, and narratives of social conflict.
Peter Andrew Lusztyk is a Canadian artist who uses photography to turn ordinary and overlooked things into something beautiful and full of details.
Uwe Ommer is a German photographer. His biggest project was based on the idea of documenting all types of families on every continent.
Andrew Prokos is an American fine art photographer whose works incorporate architectural elements and sweeping natural and urban views.
Magda von Hanau is a Brazilian artist who works in drawing, photography, installations, and sculpture; spanning movements, mediums, and cultures.
Terry O'Neill was an English photographer. He gained renown documenting the fashions, styles, and celebrities of the 1960s.
Brian Donnelly aka KAWS is an American artist best known for designing limited edition toys and clothing, inspired by the iconic pop culture characters.
Md Tokon is a Bangladesh-born and New York-based contemporary painter whose works are purely abstract and have a great touch of impressionism.
Widely known for his fashion-related photos and Vogue association, Horst P. Horst is one of the monumental photographers of the 20th century.
Kyong Lee is a Korean abstract artist whose work reconciles physical and emotional realities through an exploration of color, material, process, and form.
Natasha Zupan is an American artist whose work explores the manipulation of surface texture, light and the interweaving of time.
Mauricio Velez is a Colombian photographer whose images are meant to refine the sensitivity and perception of the viewer towards art and the human body.
David Burdeny is a Canadian photographer whose works occupy an artistic middle ground between the concrete and the spiritual.
Chad Kleitsch is an American photographer and educator. He has taught Photography at Bard College, Yale University, and Sarah Lawrence College.
Markus Klinko is an award-winning celebrity photographer and director, who has worked with many eminent movie and fashion stars.
Trained in interior architecture and photography, Arslan Sükan is a Turkish artist who tackles ideas that question the limitations of human perception.
Rick Lewis is an American contemporary artist who works as an abstract painter, drawer, printmaker, photographer, and sculptor.
Jose Sierra is a Colombian artist whose body of work continues to be based around his self-representation from which he addresses a homoerotic gaze.
Alice de Kruijs is a Dutch fine-art photographer who explores the subject of identity and diversity, aiming to go against the standard ideals.
An American action painter, Raymond Hendler created a unique style of abstract pictograms that blend a personal language with hints at figuration.
Margaret Morrison is an American artist, best known for her paintings which fuse still life, elements from figurative art and subjects of surrealism.
Dimitri Likissas is a highly-talented Belgian-born artist who explores the unlimited potential of chromatic and tonal scale in his dot paintings.
One of the leading figures in American art since the 1960s, Robert Indiana played a pivotal role in the growth of assemblage art, hard-edge painting and Pop Art.

Hunt Slonem is an American painter, sculptor, and printmaker. He is best known for his Neo-Expressionist paintings of tropical birds, often based on a personal aviary in which he has been keeping from 30 to over 100 live birds of various species.
Stanley Boxer was an American artist best known for thickly painted abstract works of art. He was also an accomplished sculptor and print-maker.
Damien Hirst is one of the most known and wealthiest living contemporary artists, creating notorious work that marked the art of Britain in the 1990s.
Alex Hodge is an American contemporary artist who uses the medium of sculpture and clay as the conduit for processing her experience in the world.
Linling Lu is a Chinese contemporary artist widely known for her hard-edge, circular abstract paintings with concentric rings of color.
Clara Fialho is a Brazilian-American artist known for her use of bold, bright colors that instinctively attract the eye to her work.
Angelica Tcherassi is a Colombian abstract artist and product designer. Born in Barranquilla, she has lived in Barcelona since 2003.
Dora Franco is a famous Colombian photographer who started her career working in Fashion & Beauty and Interior photography.
Susan Breen is an American artist who creates beautiful abstract paintings. Growing up in Buffalo, New York she showed interest in art from a very early age.
Lawrence Larry Zox was an American painter known for his work in the color field movement of the 1960s.
James Lewin is a self-taught British photographer whose goal is to present African Wildlife in an immersive and striking manner.
Isabelle van Zeijl is an internationally well-known photographer recognized for her ability to create striking self-portraits with depth and meaning.
Jane Waterous is an internationally acclaimed Canadian contemporary artist whose work spans an array of mediums and techniques.
Pierre Muckensturm is a French abstract artist whose visual language is built around softly textured surfaces and a muted, black and white palette.
Dmitri Wright is an American contemporary artist whose both current and past work has been labeled as abstract impressionist.
Frederick J. Brown was an American visual artist arguably best known for his extensive portrait series of jazz and blues musicians.
Koray Erkaya is a Turkish artist who began his professional career as a photographer three decades ago, working in fashion and advertisement.
Throughout his career, the Mexican contemporary artist Méndez Blake has been exploring the possible relations between literature and fine arts.
Interested in playing with memory and relating it to the present, Paloma Castello is a Colombian photographer born in Bogotá.
Syd Solomon is best known for works illustrating his fascination with the climatic and overall environmental conditions of land, sea, and sky.
James Walsh is an American painter known for dazzling paintings characterized by vibrant color pallet and fluidity reminiscent of post war abstraction.
Won Lee is a Korean-born and Canada-based contemporary artist who creates sculptures, paintings, and drawings. His main subject matter is the human figure.
Kyle Andrew Szpyrka is an American contemporary artist whose paintings are based on the journey of self-discovery and spiritual awakening.
Mira Schendel was a Brazilian artist, considered one of the most significant Latin American artists of the 20th century.
Paul Snell combines traditional and digital techniques to explore the possibilities of abstraction and minimalism in contemporary photo-media.
Armando de la Garza is a Mexican contemporary artist who began studying painting at an early age and started his professional art career at 22.
Luca Artioli is an Italian artist, poet, and photographer, known around the world. Born in Milan, he has been living in Miami since 2008.
Michael Knigin was an American painter and printmaker, particularly well versed in screenprinting and known as a master of lithography.
Anthony James is a British/American artist widely known and recognized for his monumental and experiential sculptures and installations.
Alex Katz is an American painter and printmaker renowned for his simplified approach that examines the limitations of portraits and landscapes.
Billy Ma is a contemporary artist born in Taiwan and raised in Canada who uses his unique heritage to make characteristic and border breaking pieces of art.
Born in Italy, Francesca Piqueras is a French photographer interested in objects man makes for the purposes of economy and war.
Margaret Roleke is an American mixed media artist focusing on issues such as racism, gun violence, global warming, and an assault on the truth.
Peter Max is a German-born American illustrator and graphic artist, known for the use of psychedelic shapes and color palettes as well as spectra in his work.
Mr. Brainwash – often written MBW – is a name used by Paris-born, Los Angeles-based self-proclaimed filmmaker and street artist Thierry Guetta.
Marc Lagrange was a Belgian photographer whose work celebrates fantasies and desire, focusing on the female beauty. Lagrange was born in Kinshasa, Congo.
An American Abstract Expressionist painter, Frank Wimberley is celebrated for his dynamic paintings that evoke the movement of jazz.

Rodrigo Spinel is a Colombian artist who uses drawing as a way to explore the relevance of detail in the construction of images, objects and spaces.
Nikolaos Schizas is a Greek artist based in Barcelona, who creates dynamic abstract paintings that radiate with vibrant splashes of color.

A sculptor at heart, Susan Woldman is an American contemporary artist who brings the sculpting sensibility into her paintings.

Paul Manes is an American contemporary painter whose ability to handle oil paint allows for fluidity of style between abstraction and representation.

Francis Bacon was an Irish-born British painter, known for his raw, emotionally charged images. He created in Expressionism, Surrealism and Cubism.
Collin van der Sluijs is a Dutch illustrator artist and gallery owner whose work features beautiful portraiture of children and little furry creatures
Thierry Noir is the man to whom we owe the longest concrete painting in the world. His paintings, with their bright colors and their melancholy poetry, represent nowadays the art of the Berlin wall.
Christopher Wool is an American contemporary artist known for a conceptual, abstract and purified, mostly black and white, text based works.

Kour Pour is British/Iranian artist who deals with the concept of Persian tribal textile designs synthesizing the traditional cultural patterns into paintings representing the rituals of the animal hunt with vibrant colors and faded symbolism.
Anders Gjennestad is a Norwegian stencil artist also know as STRØK. He is recognized by multi-layered stencil work that contains extraordinary details.
Wayne Thiebaud is an American Pop art painter celebrated for his vivid pictures of mundane objects like pies, lipsticks, paint cans and gumball machines.
Martin Kippenberger was born in 1953. Known as the provocative, and one of the most influential German artists of the post-war era.
One of the most prominent sculptors of his generation, Anish Kapoor is an Indian artist known for his intense outdoor and indoor site-specific works.
Wade Guyton  is a printmaker best known for his black monochromes made with an Epson inkjet printer.
Vik Muniz is a Brazilian visual artist who incorporates the use of everyday objects such as sugar, chocolate, wires and recyclables in his paintings.
Russell Young  is a British artist best known for his compelling larger than life screenprint images from history and popular culture.
Friedensreich Hundertwasser was an Austrian artist best known for his unique vivid style and architecture in accordance with nature.
Grayson Perry is a British artist whose life has indelibly shaped his work, make him one of the most incisive commentators of the contemporary society and culture.
Djordje Ozbolt is a Serbian-born artist, now based in London, known for bizarre compositions and eclectic style in his paintings and sculptures.

Peter Zimmermann is a Contemporary Abstract artist known for his blob paintings. His medium is typically airbrushing combined with digital arts; he mainly uses programs such as Photoshop to express his unique point of view.
Niki de Saint Phalle was a French sculptor, painter and filmmaker, renowned for her large sculptures of Nanas, voluptuous females.
Lygia Clark was a Brazilian artist best known for her painting and installation work through which she tested ideas about multisensory and participatory art.
Jacques Lipchitz, born Chaim Jacob Lipschitz, was the Lithuanian-born French artist best known for the Cubist works he made in Paris during the early 1900s.
Rick Begneaud is an American mixed-media artist, whose art is recognized for his use of found objects – scraps of materials and fabrics.
Francisco Toledo was a Mexican artist, painter and sculptor who worked in various media: pottery, sculpture, painting, weaving, and graphic arts.
Dennis Hare, born in California, is an American self-taught artist, well known for his abstract and figurative paintings, drawings and sculptures.
Stefan Thiel is a German artist who uses a binary system in his works: he transfers photographs into silhouettes.
Theodoros Stamos, was a Greek-American artist. He is one of the youngest painters of the original group of abstract expressionist painters...
Marcel Broodthaers was a Belgian poet, an experimental filmmaker and a visual artist known for his witty approach to creating diverse pieces of art
Joseph Fernand Henri Léger was a French painter, sculptor, and filmmaker who was deeply influenced by modern industrial technology and Cubism.
Ernest Trova was a self-trained American surrealist and pop art painter and sculptor known for his signature image and figure series, The Falling Man.
Piero Dorazio was an Italian painter, known for his linear, atmospheric paintings of grids crisscrossed with fluid brushstrokes and pulsating in color and texture.
Rirkrit Tiravanija is a contemporary Thai artist, best known for his intimate installations that allow people to socialize, share meals, read, play music, or cook.
Conrad Marca-Relli was an American artist, a member of New York School Abstract Expressionist artists and leading art movement of the postwar era.
Eddie Peake is a British artist whose varied artistic vocabulary encompasses performance, video, photography, painting, sculpture and installation.
Richard Hambleton was a Canadian street and conceptual artist, known for Mass Murder Images and Shadowman, his most successful series of paintings.
Louis Icart, born in 1888 in Toulouse, was a French artist famous for his paintings, etchings, engravings and illustrations.
Mary Stevenson Cassatt was an American painter and printmaker who created images of the lives of women, and bonds between mothers and children.
Milton Avery was an American artist, known for his his paintings created in Modern art. His work is representational and focuses on color relations.
Charles Bell was an American Photorealist and Hyperrealist painter, known for his large scale still lifes arranged in imaginary scenes and dynamic compositions.
William Wegman is an American artist best known for creating series of compositions involving dogs, primarily his own Weimaraners in various costumes and poses.
Born as Angel Ortiz, American artist LA II is one of the iconic graffiti artists from the Lower East Side, also known by his collaboration with Haring.
Pavlos is a Greek artist, born in the south of Peloponesia at Filiatra in 1930. The artist explores the surface of the everyday. He lives in France.
Hank O’Neal is an American artist, a photographer who compiled a legacy of one of the most vital and significant movements in the world of art.
Matti Braun is a German contemporary artist born in 1968. He works in diverse artistic expressions: installations, objects, photography and painting.
Abraham Walkowitz was a Russian-American Modernist painter, best-known for his series of watercolors depicting Isadora Duncan, a pioneer of modern dance.
Mark Powell is a London-based artist born in 1980, noted for his life-like Biro pen drawings, done on vintage documents, manuscripts, and postcards.
One of the greatest living sculptors of the modern era, Arturo Di Modica created monumental sculptures.
Jean Dufy was a French painter who managed to merge the essentials of cubism, fauvism and impressionism into his colorful artwork.
MARS-1 aka Mario Martinez is an American painter who depicts large, extraterrestrial looking landscapes and spatial distortion.
Although known widely as a singer, a songwriter, and a co-founder of the Beatles, John Lennon displayed a great affection towards the visual art form even before his musical display.
Aiiroh is a French contemporary artist widely known for his Pop Art inspired street art. He’s been drawing and painting from an early age.
An artist of diverse practices, Gao Weigang is a Chinese author who produces paintings, installations, sculptures and performance works.
Sara Pittman is an abstract painter who uses transparent layers of paint to portray numerous natural elements including woodlands and longhorn skulls.
Adriana Oliver is a Spanish figurative artist born in 1990, in Barcelona. She currently lives and works in Los Angeles.
Lawrence Schiller is an American artist whose rich body of work spans from photography and nonfiction writing to directing Oscar-winning films.
Philippe Alfieri was an Italian-American artist. He lived in Newark and in Queens and was a member of the Arts Students League of NYC.
Charles Uzzell-Edwards is a British graffiti artist known by the moniker "Pure Evil" best known for his signature fanged bunnies and is a stablemate of Banksy.
Nick Walker is a British established graffiti artist credited with introducing stencil graffiti to Bristol in the early 1990s, helping develop the movement since.
Vhils is the alias of a Portuguese street artist Alexandre Farto whose remarkably unique technique of plaster penetration makes his work immediately recognizable.
Chris Ellis, otherwise known as DAZE, is a graffiti artist and a painter that made a successful transition from the street art to the gallery walls.
George Condo is an influential American artist who combines two seemingly unblendable worlds - avant-garde painting techniques and Pop-art themes.
Niels Shoe Meulman is an Dutch visual artist, graffiti writer, graphic designer, art director and a graphic designer.
Sowat is a French artist - a screenwriter, film director and graffiti artist best known for his calligraffiti style.
Exploring new techniques and discussing various media, Brusk is a French artist known for his dripping style that combines a calligraphic work in 3D, characters and tagging.
Pichi & Avo is a renowned graffiti duo from Spain that produces a spectacular explosion of fresh colors and impressions. They create breathtaking figurative detail and quality.
Iranian street art brothers, Icy and Sot, after living for just two years in USA, have developed a rich portfolio of urban stencils that address global social issues.
Bruce Nauman is an American artist whose practice spans a broad range of media that has inspired many contemporary artists of the 20th century.
Famous for his signature style of Boterismo, Fernando Botero is a Colombian painter that depicts people and figures in exaggerated and distorted volumes.
Thomas Struth is a renowned photographer from Germany who is known for his complex images of urban scenes, vivid jungles and group portraits.
Julie Mehretu is a Ethiopian-born, American-based artist famous for abstract printmaking and painting, relying on her unique method of layering.
Martin Whatson is a Norwegian stencil artist, born in 1984. He is known for his grey toned stencil works as a basis for adding vibrant colors to break the monochrome concrete expression.
Alison Jackson is an English spoof photographer, born in 1970, best known for her lookalike images of celebrities posed in private moments.
Marino Marini was an Italian graphic artist, painter, and sculptor best known for his series of stylized equestrian statues.
Adolph Gottlieb was an American painter, born on March 14, 1903 in New York. He is known as a pioneer of the Abstract Expressionism movement.
As French painter and theorist, Georges Mathieu is considered the founder of Lyrical Abstraction and is also associated with Tachism.
Katharina Grosse is a German artist best known for her spray-painted installations which cover gallery walls, furniture and hanging plastic orbs with a surface of lustrous, vivid colors.
Janet Fish is an American painter, best known for her still life paintings, with renewed focus on the effects of light and reflection on familiar subjects.
Barry McGee is an American painter and graffiti artist best known for his moniker Twist and his  mixed-media installations inspired by urban culture.
Igor Mitoraj was an eminent Polish sculptor whose classicism combined technical abilities with a certain postmodern malaise.
Wolfgang Tillmans is a German documentary-style photographer, with a focal point on London’s gay community. He studied at Bournemouth and Poole College of Art and Design in England from 1990 to 1992.
Komar and Melamid is an tandem team of Russian conceptualist artists Vitaly Komar, born 1943 and Alexander Melamid, born in 1945
Peter Halley is an American painter and printmaker, best known for geometric abstractions, is associated with the Minimalist and Neo-Geo movements.
Jack Pierson is an American artist and draftsman best known for his photography, abstract sculptures, and collages.
Romero Britto is a Brazilian painter and sculptor who successfully combines elements of Cubism and Pop art into his extremely positive and colorful work.
Louise Nevelson was one of the most prominent American female sculptors of the 20th century who worked during the dominance of Abstract Expressionism.

Matteo Negri is an Italian visual artist, recognized for creating various works of art. He concentrates his artistic research on different materials as marble, ceramic and resin, mixing them with a pop range of hues as an expressive instrument.

Lynda Benglis is an American sculptor and visual artist, considered as a pioneer of a form of abstraction in which each work is the result of materials in action, creating sculptures that eschew minimalist reserve in favor of bold colors and sensual line.
Joseph Cornell, born in Nyack, New York in 1903, is best known for his shadow boxes and experimental films, and his association with the Surrealist group of artists.
Carolyn Marks Blackwood is a New York-based fine art photographer who has a knack for capturing the natural world and the beauty that lies therein.
Kunstrasen is a German stencil artist who derives his name from the German term for astroturf, or a surface of synthetic fibres made to look like natural grass.
Boicut, is an Austrian artist whose illustrative work combines impulsive lines and shapes.
Richard Ernst Artschwager was an American painter, illustrator and sculptor. His work has associations with Pop Art, Conceptual art and Minimalism.
Charles Arnoldi is an American painter, sculptor, and printmaker best known for his brightly colored, abstract paintings that incorporate wood.
Olafur Eliasson is a Danish-Icelandic artist known for large-scale installation art with elemental materials to enhance the viewer’s experience.
James Coignard was a French painter, ceramist, sculptor and etcher, born in Tours in 1925. He lived and worked in Antibes, in the Maritime Alps.
Rembrandt van Rijn was a Dutch artist who is generally considered one of the greatest painters in European art and the most important in Dutch history
Wassily Kandinsky was an influential Russian art theorist, and the author of the first modern paintings that were created on full abstraction concepts.
John Gerrard is an Irish artist who uses computer graphics also used in the entertainment industry to create digital simulations.
Giorgio de Chirico was an Italian artist, known for enigmatic paintings of the 1910s and 1920s, and his profound influence on the Surrealist movement.
Patrick Hughes is a British contemporary artist born in 1939, best known for his original concept of  Reverspective paintings and wall reliefs.
Chris Levine is a Canadian artist, a pioneer in the field of light art, creating and adapting technology in the pursuit of visual sensations.
Angel Otero is an Puerto Rican artist whose work is characterized by an interest in personal history, expressionistic abstraction, and Spanish Baroque.
Fiona Rae is a British abstract artist born in 1963, counted among the Young British Artists (YBA) who rose to prominence in the 1990s.
Gerald Ogilvie Laing was a British pop artist and sculptor. He lived in the Scottish Highlands. He was born in 1936 and died in 2011.
Currier & Ives was a successful American printmaking firm that produced prints from paintings by fine artists as black and white lithographs that were hand colored.
Crystal Wagner is a contemporary interdisciplinary artist, who aims at creating organic bioforms, using materials that people are exposed to.
Hermann Nitsch was an Austrian artist who worked in experimental and multimedia modes and was known for his intensive fascination with religion.
Eugène Leroy was a French painter born in 1910. From the 1940s onward he exhibited regularly, primarily in France and Belgium but also abroad.
Crail Moansburg is a Dutch artist known for his colorful and expressive screenprints made in his studio in the Karl Marx Factory in The Hague.
Ralph Goings, born in California in 1928, is an American painter closely associated with the Photorealism movement of the late 1960s and early 1970s.
Hajime Sorayama is a Japanese illustrator, known for his precisely detailed, erotic hand painted portrayals of women and feminine robots.
Reginald Marsh was an American painter, born in Paris, most notable for his depictions of life in New York City in the 1920s and 1930s.
Max Bill was an architect, artist, painter, typeface designer, industrial designer and graphic designer. He was born in Winterthur, Switzerland.
K-Guy is a British artist, born in 1966. He is known for his thought-provoking works and street art. He frequently uses found and discarded objects.
Gerard Ernest Schneider was a Swiss artist born in 1896. He was one of the major pioneers of Lyrical Abstraction, a gestural and personal form of abstraction.
Carlos Cruz-Diez was a Franco-Venezuelan artist, a major protagonist in the field of Kinetic and Optical art. He lived, worked and died in Paris.
Henri Michaux was a Belgian-born painter born in 1899. He is well known for his painting, poetry and prose. Michaux later took French citizenship.
Josef Hoflehner is an Austrian artist known for his landscape photographs taken in some of the most remote areas of the world.
Ibram Lassaw was an American Abstract Expressionist artist, famous for his sculptures made of bronze, silver, copper, and steel.
Don Nice was an American artist whose work reminds to the 19th-century encyclopedic illustrations and its meticulous precision, created by artists such as Audubon or Ernst Haeckel.
Sarah Hardacre is a British artist mostly known for her collages and prints featuring 20th-century architecture and women from vintage magazines.
Irony is a British graffiti artist, active mostly around the London's Camden Town. He often collaborates with other street artists, such as Boe and Candie.
Kenro Izu is a Japanese photographer born in 1949, known for his elegant still lifes, nudes, and Sacred Places series of images.
O'Clock is the pseudonym of one of the most productive and the most creative artists in the history of Parisian graffiti scene.
Burton Morris is an American artist, known for his pop art paintings with bright and graphic elements of pop culture. He uses bold lines and vivid colors.
Primarily an award-winning sculptor and graphic artist, Waltercio Caldas﻿ has been known to produce sketches, paintings, and installation art.
Lee Jaffe is an American photographer, painter and movie producer, interested in the topics of social marginalization.
Influenced by both post-war contemporary art and popular culture, Tomokazu Matsuyama is a Japanese painter who uses colorful acrylic on canvases.
Artist Andre Masson was a French Surrealist painter and graphic artist. He was one of the foremost practitioners of automatic writing
Norman Rockwell was an American artist who painted numerous pictures for story illustrations, advertising campaigns, posters, and books.
Michael De Feo is best known as an American street artist who makes ubiquitous and iconic flower images and urban interventions in many international environments.
Charles Cham is a Malaysian painter whose puzzlingly primitive artworks resemble the images from the walls of prehistoric caves.
Maaike Bakker is a Pretoria-based artist and illustrator who works in a many different media including drawing, sculpture and installation.
Alison Saar is an American artist who explores themes of African cultural diaspora and spirituality through her paintings, sculptures, and installations.
Sarah Moon, born Marielle Warin in 1941, is a French photographer known for her elegant photographs that are almost abstract in their painterly qualities.
Andy Moses is an American artist known for his inimitable take on color and the relationship between space, shape and light.
Born in 1910 in Philadelphia, Joseph Hirsch was an American artist associated with the Social Realism genre of the 1920s and 1930s.
Leonardo Drew is an African American contemporary artist based in Brooklyn, New York, who creates amazing installation pieces.
Since the 1990s, Brian Calvin has developed a body of highly stylized flattened paintings, rendering his figures in light-soaked portraits that retain a lifelike quality.
Seth Armstrong is an American artist, based in Los Angeles, famous for his hyper-realistic paintings in which he depicts his surroundings.
Nancy Gifford is an American painter and an installation artist whose creative vocabulary is mainly concerned with unconventional ways of establishing narratives.
Budd Hopkins was a distinguished Abstract Expressionist painter, sculptor, and prominent figure in alien abduction phenomena and related UFO research.
Sophia Vari is a well-known Greek artist specialized in bronze sculpture, as well as in collages, oils, and watercolors.
Jerkface is an American artist currently based in New York, NY. He is known for his colorful murals often depicting cartoon characters.
John Ferren was an American artist whose abstract paintings were influenced by both Wassily Kandinsky and Zen Buddhism.
Roberta Morzetti is an Italian artist whose work exposes us to an art production that transforms materials into incredible sculptures.
The Chinese contemporary artist Wang Ai is known for delicate paintings made with rice paper, tea, Chinese ink and special pencils.
Marko Tadic is one of the most prominent Croatian artists of the younger generation, whose practice spans installation, drawing, and animation.
George McNeil created works that ranged from entirely abstract to loosely representational, always commanding a mastery technique.
Amy Bennett creates paintings of interior scenes and rural and suburban landscapes, populating them with figures acting out  snippets of narratives.
An American artist, Annie Lapin creates abstract paintings grounded in representation, providing the viewer with a sensation of a shifting grounds.
An American conceptual artist, Ryan Brown's practice spans performances, paintings, sculptures, photographic series, and installations.
Jim Jonson was an American painter whose main artistic goal was to capture and display the phenomenon of motion present in a sports event.
Lou Ros is a self-taught French painter with a rich graffiti background. He paints instinctively, following the footsteps of the expressionists who fascinate him.
A British contemporary artist born in 1959, Sasha Holzer is known for his carefully carved wooden panels.
A Brazilian multimedia artist, Cinthia Marcelle uses her mediums to document the effects that her interventions have on the usual order of things.
A member of Grupo Frente and professor at Museu de Arte Moderna, Ivan Serpa was one of the most important contributors to Brazilian Concretism and Neo-Concretism.
Montez Magno is part of a generation that, despite facing political difficulties in the 1960s and 70s, managed to reexamine modernity and trace other paths to its crossroads.
Sarah Grilo was an Argentinian abstract painter, now considered as one of the most important Latin American artists of the 20th century.
A Canadian contemporary artist, An Whitlock creates work spanning painting, sculpture and installation art.
Alex Racine is an American contemporary sculptor. He has earned a Bachelor of Fine Arts for Sculpture from the School of Visual Art, New York.
Guy Charon is a French artist widely known for his vibrantly colored landscape paintings and lithographs, similar to Fauvism and Modernism.
Jessica Rice was a Belgian painter whose themes included native Flemish landscapes, family gatherings, crowded restaurants, craftsmen and domestic scenes.
Aaron Fink is an American contemporary artist who works in a variety of mediums, including oil, sculpture, and works on paper.
Constantin Antonovici was a Romanian sculptor whose most famous motif was an owl. He was a disciple of Constantin Brancusi.
An American photographer, Richard Ham is widely known and recognized for his studio portraits of famous artist Pablo Picasso.
Arnold Weber was a prolific American artist who produced thousands of oil and watercolor paintings. He was born and raised in the Bronx.
Muhammad Ali was an American professional boxer, activist, and philanthropist. A son of the church muralist, Ali also created art occasionally.
Shlomo Katz was a Polish-born Israeli artist best known for his painting skills. His talent for drawing was apparent from an early age.
Ginny Masters is an American artist whose preferred medium is watercolor on paper. Her paintings are inspired by nature and she often depicts flowers.
Paul Chelko was an American artist known for abstract painting, ultra-realism, portraiture, performance art, music, poetry and film.
Igor Tabakov is a Russian photographer. He has worked 20 years as a head photographer and photo editor for The Moscow Times.
Oskar D'Amico was an Italian artist who had three major periods in his artistic life: Figurative, Materic and Geometric.
Manuel Felguérez Barra was a Mexican contemporary artist. He did most of his studies in France, where he specialized in abstract art.
A barber by profession and without any formal artistic education, José Antonio Velásquez became the first and foremost Honduran primitivist painter.
Bernard Greenwald is an American contemporary painter whose primary concern is color. He received his BFA from the Philadelphia Museum, College of Art.
Peter Lik is an Australian photographer, best known for his landscape works - cascading waterfalls, ethereal mountain peaks and peaceful desert canyons.
Wayne Ensrud is an American painter and educator, perhaps best known for his landscapes, lifestyles and aesthetics of wine and food.
A French furniture designer and interior designer, Pierre Paulin is celebrated for his innovative interior and seating furniture design.
Mirkò Guida is an Italian contemporary painter. Trained as a graphic artist, he considers his work to be more graphic than pictorial.
Babe Shapiro was an American artist widely known for his abstract and Op Art paintings. His artistic career spanned almost six decades.
Charles Ford is an American artist widely known for his photorealistic paintings. His subjects are urban environments such as shops and city streets.
Tony Marsh is an American contemporary artist whose primary form of artistic expression is the ceramic vessel. He is based in Long Beach, California.
Jason Hallman is an American artist known for his paintings, layered one on top of the other, building up a timeline of acrylic geology.
Lauren Mabry is an American contemporary artist from Madison, Wisconsin, who creates ceramic objects, vessels, and dimensional glaze paintings.
J. Kevin White is an American photographer widely known and recognized for his imagery of rural life on the coast of Maine.
Born in São Caetano do Sul, Thomaz Rosa is a Brazilian contemporary painter whose works are based on points and concrete forms, verbal analogies of images.
Tamara Dean is an Australian photographer, installation and video artist, who explores the relationship between humans and the natural world.
Linde Ivimey is an Australian artist widely known for her figural sculptures depicting human-animal hybrids, usually animal heads on clothed human bodies.
Danie Mellor is an Australian artist whose multidisciplinary practice explores the intersections of contemporary and historic culture.
Melvin Grave Guzman is an American contemporary artist born in Harlem, New York, working in photography, performance, and monumental mixed-media.
Born in Atlanta, Georgia, Vernon O’Meally is an American contemporary artist based in New York, known for his paintings, sculptures, and installations.
David Phelps is an American contemporary artist whose figurative sculptures, ranging up to three times life-size, appear to emerge from the ground.
Using traditional techniques from painting, Ken Rausch is an American artist known for his exciting and richly colored wall sculptures.
Born in Guangdong, Calvin Teng is a Taiwanese contemporary artist widely known and recognized for his serene abstract paintings.
Danny Ferrell is an American painter whose works represent fantasies and fears about the ‘Other’ through depictions of the everyday queer male.
Ben Zank is an American photographer whose images often conveniently stage himself as the main character. He is known for using props, such as yellow tape.
Raymond Saá is a Cuban-American artist whose paintings and works on paper form a complex, multilayered formal environment for the viewer to decipher.
Chaz Guest is an American contemporary artist who specializes in figurative painting, concentrating on portraiture and cultural narratives.

Maruch Santíz Gómez is a Mayan Mexican photographer, writer, embroidery and textile designer, and actress, involved in cultural projects since the 1980s.
Charis Entwisle is a British artist whose practice focuses on painting and drawing, depicting wistful characters and dreamlike yet sincere scenes.
Charlie Haydn Taylor is a British artist whose work addresses various subjects within the political, social, and psychological spheres.
Stela Vasileva is a Bulgarian artist based in Sofia, working in the fields of contemporary drawing, 3D objects, and installations.
With ceramics as a base material, Svetli Evgeniev is a Bulgarian multidisciplinary artist whose predominant motives are simplicity and minimalism.
Stefano Trappolini is an Italian artist whose research mainly focuses on painting and video art, though he also works in the field of photography.
Alan Brown is an American artist known for using curious found objects, often items that have long outlived their known purpose or identity.
Lyoudmila Milanova is a Bulgarian contemporary artist whose work revolves around natural phenomena, technology, and time.
Always imagining and creating, Arnaud Laly is a French graphic designer and artist who approaches his work via triptych: line – pattern – flat colors.
Compulsive and spontaneous, Valco is a French self-taught artist who evolves his street-art and pop-art works through emotions and research.
Franck Célaire is a French architect and artist who grew up with a pencil in his hand amidst comic book characters and cartoons.
Iskra Blagoeva is a Bulgarian contemporary artist. Although she prefers painting in particular, she uses various other media.
Born in Bosnia and Herzegovina, Mirza Cizmic is an artist currently residing in Helsinki. He has also lived and studied in Sarajevo and Munka-Ljungby.
Miles Regis is a Trinidad-born artist whose large-scale mixed media paintings on canvas and linen incorporate dimensional collage elements.
Having previously worked in cinema, Gaia Adducchio is an Italian artist who currently uses photography as her primary tool of expression.
Lorenzo Swinton is an American artist specializing in abstract and contemporary paintings using acrylics as his force for invigorating visuals.
Sam Heydt is an American social practice and recycled media artist working in media such as film, video, installation, photography, sculpture, and sound.
Lin Zhipeng, also known as No.223, is one of the leading figures of new Chinese photography, popularizing his work originally via social media.
Jaggu Prasad is an Indian contemporary artist who uses paintbrushes with only a single otter hair to capture intricate details.
Line Street is a French artist whose work revolves around small colored and funny ghosts, called BOU. These pieces bring positivity and and joy to viewers.
Inspired by traditional Portuguese art, Befa is a French artist whose style is characterized by its simple shapes, bright colors and geometric patterns.
Ceel Mogami de Haas is a Dutch multidisciplinary artist whose work spans a range of media, including sculpture, drawing, writing, installation, and video art.
Diyano Purwadi is an Indonesian contemporary artist whose work is based on social, cultural, and political phenomena he observes around himself.
George Byrne is an Australian artist whose photographs juxtapose the vivid clarity of modernist painting against the New Topographics photography movement.
Patrik Grijalvo is an artist working with analog architectural photos, assembling layered works from various images of a single piece of architecture.
Lawrence Morrell is an American sculptor whose visual and tactile works physically show the negative and positive effects of humans on this planet.
Lena Ditlmann is a German contemporary artist whose abstract motifs are made up of fine lines that she weaves into one another.
Diane DallasKidd is an American artist who’s always searching to draw something new and unexpected from the medium with a focus on process.
Wayne Levin is an American photographer arguably best known for his black-and-white underwater photographs of swimmers and marine life.
Paul Bloch is an American artist whose sculptures are improvisational. His primary material is stone. Bloch studied anthropology, sculpture, and music.
Alex Weinstein is an American multidisciplinary artist engaged in painting, sculpture, film, and creative writing. He lives and works in Southern California.
Mio Yamato is a Japanese artist whose dot-based works are organic, embracing the passage of time and the reality of the body.
Andrew Millner is an American artist whose work is inspired and centered on nature. He started drawing on the computer in 2005.
Sabine Friesicke is a German artist whose works on paper and canvas have the goal of visualizing experienced time as well as the process of time going by.
Donald Groscost is an American contemporary artist whose primary interest lies in the observation of natural phenomena and the systems they inhabit.
Pierre Marie Brisson is a French artist who uses a collage technique, combining various elements in his compositions. He was born in Orléans.

Born in Paris, Eugène Barricade is a French street artist who works mostly on atypical and urban supports using the stencil technique.
Tunji Adeniyi-Jones is a British contemporary artist known for vibrant swirls of color and an eye towards West African aesthetics.
Jordan Kerwick is a self-taught Australian artist who translates three-dimensional space into flattened compositions of pattern and color.
Marina Mankarios is a Franco-Egyptian sculptor. She developed an artistic sensibility at a very young age with intense cello and theater practice.
Tania Dibbs is an American artist who explores the jagged intersection between the natural world, humanity and culture through painting and sculpture.
Hideaki Yamanobe is a Japanese contemporary painter whose works bring together traditions of Western painting with influences from his Asian culture.
Catherine Seher is a French artist whose visual universe is centered on the human figure, exuding a powerful sense of anonymity and isolation.
Sergio Femar is a Spanish artist who uses construction waste materials, adding sustainability to the list of topics he explores.
Ai Haibara is a Japanese contemporary sculptor known for her distinctive style that fuses traditional wood sculpting and acrylic paint.
Sweetieboosh is an American artist known for her animal sculptures and figures. She chose animals because of their great symbolic importance.
Ficre Ghebreyesus was an Eritrean-American artist who operated fluidly between abstraction and figuration, creating oil and acrylic paintings.
Charlotte Zinsser is an American artist driven by her location within systems, ephemerality, sublimity, and the things she can see but does not know.
Anna Barham is a British multidisciplinary artist working across video, sound, print, installation, and performance. She lives and works in London.
Adam Riches is a British painter and draughtsman widely known for his characteristically stylized portraits and figurative works.
Born in Nantes, Pez is a French illustrator, painter and graphic designer, best known for his surrealistic, finely detailed works.
Bernard Zawisa was an American artist widely known for his geometric abstract paintings, abstract figuratives, and texture paintings.
Jim Perry is an American artist whose sculptures are known for their graceful curves, torqued tensions and sensuous materiality.
Sarah J. Edwards is a British photographer. She often works together with her twin sister, Sally J. Edwards, who is an Art Director.
Dejvid Knežević is a Slovenian contemporary artist, a dotted inker or what's more often referred to as a stippling illustrator.
Drawn to the face because of its inherent psychological weight, Danielle Coenen is an American artist widely known for her portraits.

Thomas Downing was an American abstract painter, known for his clear, dotted paintings. He was associated with the Washington Color Field Movement.
Pablo Atchugarry is a Uruguayan sculptor, noted for his marble work, like public pieces in several towns in Lombardy. He lives in Italy and Uruguay.
Lawrence Weiner is an American artist, who greatly contributed to the formation of conceptual art. His work takes the form of typographic text.
John Armleder is a Swiss performance artist, painter, sculptor, critic and curator primarily known for his involvements with Fluxus and the Neo-Geo group.
Valerio Adami  is an Italian painter who addresses politics in his art, incorporating modern European history, literature, philosophy, and mythology.
Pez or El Pez (The Fish in Spanish) is a Barcelona-born artist who began his artistic career on the streets of his hometown in 1999.
A true legend of Belgian art history and Surrealism, Rene Magritte was one of the most innovative and unique painters that emerged from the 20th-century art.
Cornelia Parker is a British contemporary artist born in 1956, known for her works created in a range of mediums – from sculpture, installation, and works on paper, to photographs.
Jane Hammond is an American painter, sculptor, and printmaker living and working in New York. Her art is often based on dreams and literature.
Ellen Gallagher is an American contemporary artist who examines the development of African-American stereotypes through a range of media.
A leading figure of the post-war avant-garde scene, John Cage was an American composer, music theorist, philosophical writer and a visual artist.
Ron Davis, born Ronald Davis in 1937, is an American painter, whose works had a significant impact on contemporary abstract painting.
Charles Burchfield was an American artist, known for dark and spooky watercolor paintings that depict highly personal images of nature and small towns.
Sérgio de Camargo was a Brazilian sculptor and relief maker best known for wall-based reliefs, public sculptures and architectural commissions.
Murray Fredericks is an Australian photographer best known for a series of color photographs and a documentary film, Salt (2009).
Dan Witz is an American street artist, active on the street art scene since the late 1970s, which makes him one of the pioneers of the movement.
Lauren Baker is a British artist known for her intriguing human-animal skull sculptures and neon lights and infinity mirror installations.
T'ang Haywen was a Chinese painter who combined the Chinese spiritual aesthetic of ink brush painting with Western abstract expressionism in his art.
Emilio Vedova was a modern Italian painter, considered one of the most important to emerge from his country's artistic scene, Arte Informale.
Wang Yan Cheng is a Chinese painter, born in Guangdong province in 1960. In 2007, the artist worked on decorating the Beijing Opera.
Matthias Schaller is a German artist who has been working on the concept of creating a variation on portrait or indirect portrait throughout his career.
Jace is a French street artist, born in 1973 in Le Havre. He is known as the creator of character Gouzou. The artist lives on Réunion Island.
Antonio Seguí is an Argentinian painter and printmaker, known for his vivid, often satirical figurative works which focus on the people of modern urban life.
Magnus Gjoen is a London-born contemporary artist who explores how something that appears destructive can be transformed into beautiful yet fragile objects of art.
Shae DeTar is an American photographer and artist, known for her wildly evocative, colorful and fiercely bold photograph-painting hybrids.
Tim Doyle is an American artist, best known for his UnReal Estate series in which he re-imagines fictional locations placed in worlds of popular television shows.
Yinka Shonibare is a British-Nigerian artist, whose work explores cultural identity, colonialism and post-colonialism.
Friedrich Heinrich Fuger was a German Neoclassical painter, recognized as one of the most important portraitist and miniaturist.
Nebay is a French artist known for his urban landscape work and his paintings from studio. Nebay is an active member of the collective JCT.
Jan Voss is a German artist who’s been living in Paris since 1960. He is quite versatile, working in painting, sculpture, engraving and ceramics.
Rosie Emerson is a British contemporary artist born in 1981, known for her depictions of enigmatic solitary women figures.

Jeanette Pasin Sloan is an American artist, best known for her photorealistic paintings, prints, and drawings of silver and stainless steel kitchenware, created in the exploration of similarities and differences between abstraction and representation.
David Bromley is a British artist known for his painting series Boys Own adventure, Female Nudes, and Butterflies. He grew up and lives in Australia.
Jorge Macchi is an Argentinian artist who combines music and painting, but also sculpture and filmmaking.
Terry Allen is an American visual artist and country musician, renown for his humorous bronze sculptures found in public places throughout the United States.
Aya Takano is a Japenese artist close to the Superflat movement. She is best known for he visions of the future and a female role in it.
Herbert Brandl is an Austrian painter. One of the members of Neue Wilde, he is known for landscape imagery executed in vibrant color and dizzying brushstrokes.
Elian (Elian artist) is an Argentinian street artist, known for his beautifully painted, bright-colored abstract compositions on huge walls.
Deborah Sengl is an Austrian artist who is exploring the questions of identity and human roles through her sculptures and installation.
Louis Masai is a London-based street artist known for his murals of endangered creatures. As a nature activist, he raises awareness of the alarming statistics.
Eric Joyner is an American painter and illustrator whose work is focused on the motifs of giant donuts and old-school tin robots.
BK FOXX is an American artist whose focus is on social awareness of animals. She is a street artist, animal lover and creator of colorful New York murals.
Max Weber was a Poland- born artist whose paintings of heavy strokes and broken lines stand between figurative and abstract expression.
Leon Ferrari was an Argentinian artist known for his provocative sculptures of different religious and political characters.
Audrey Flack is an established American artist known as one of the most influential pioneering photorealist’s of her generation and prolific sculptor.
Liliana Porter is an Argentinian artist who uses various types of media, such as photography, print making, video art and sculptural works on paper.
Bradley Theodore is a painter, born on Turks and Caicos Islands, who now lives in New York. He is mostly known for his skeletal portraits of fashion icons.
Ellen Carey is an American photographer and lens-based artist who explores abstract images with Polaroid instant technology.
Emanuele Ravagnani is an extremely versatile Italian artist, who works in collage, black and white photography, and assemblages.
Kensuke Koike is a Japanese contemporary artist, currently living in Slovenia, widely known for his exceptional skills in collage making.
Robert Silvers is an American artist known for his striking photomosaics that portray familiar images throughout history and contemporary culture.
Daniel Joseph Bombardier, better known as Denial or D3N!@L, is an Ontario-based street artist known for his sticker art campaign started in 2000.
Seaty is a French artist whose personal quest for identity and its desire for freedom led him, in the late 90s to the discovery of the Hip Hop movement.
Lu Hong is a contemporary Chinese painter who infuses western inspiration with his own techniques. His work has been exhibited worldwide.
Hailing from a Japanese-European heritage, Australian artist Nanami Cowdroy incorporates these influences in her detailed, monochromatic works.
Using the ink and color technique, a Chinese artist Yang She Wei creates paintings that question the ever-present dilemmas of modern society.
P. Gnana is a distinguished painter and sculptor in Singapore, whose colorful pieces are synonymous with the metaphorical representation of the cow.
Tian Xu Tong is a Chinese artist known for his ink paintings inspired by his interest in Zen philosophy and the Song Dynasty.
Farizwan Fajari, better known as Speak Cryptic, is a Singapore-based visual artist who uses his art to deal with issues relating to cultural identity.
Francisco Morales is an American artist who deals with conceptual and formal expositions, geometric primitivism, and organic simplicity.
Caragh Thuring is a London-based Belgian artist whose art reference the history, practice, and academic study of painting.
Mariah Robertson is an American artist known for her experimental, large-scale, abstract photographs. She lives and works in New York.
Joan Nelson is a visual artist from New York who paints epic and theatrical landscape paintings.
James Havard, born James Pinkney Havard in 1937, is an American artist known as a pioneer of abstract illusionism in the seventies.
Sakti Burman is an Indian contemporary artist, widely known and appreciated for his paintings that celebrate spirituality in every way.
Fabio Mauri was an Italian installation artist who was also rather active in the early art magazine circles.
Juno Calypso is a British photographer best known for Joyce, a series of self-portraits where she staged herself as a fictional character.
Nicholas Kriefall is an American contemporary painter whose current collection deals with the relationship between land and sea.
Jerry Schatzberg is an American photographer and filmmaker who helped shape the Hollywood Renaissance of the 1970s.
Emerson Woelffer was an American artist best known for his boldly colored abstract paintings and collages with jagged forms.
Genieve Figgis explores images from art history, that of the French pre-revolutionary Rococo period, and transforms them into figurative abstraction.
Lygia Pape was a key figure in the Concrete movement and a later co-founder of the Neo-Concrete Movement in Brazil during the 1950s and 1960s.
Roger Muhl, born Phillipe Roger Muhl, was a French painter, sculptor and draftsman, foremost considered as a painter of light and atmosphere.
Yuichi Hirako is a Japanese artist currently based in Tokyo. He earned his degree in Bachelor of Fine Arts from the Wimbledon College of Art, London.
Rebecca Mason, often working under the pseudonym "Rococo Wonderland", is an artist using light to convey the darkness within human life, existence and emotion.
Isabel Bishop was an American painter, draughtsman, and etcher born in 1902. She was best known for her graphic art and urban subject matter.
Luigi Kasimir was an Austro-Hungarian-born etcher, painter, printmaker and landscape artist.
RoamCouch, whose real name is Ryo Ogawa, is a Japanese street artist and Ukiyo-e painter. Born in Gifu, he began to draw in his childhood.
Yigal Ozeri is an acclaimed Israeli artist based in New York City, known for his large-scale cinematic portraits of young women in landscapes.
John Clem Clarke is an America artist best known for his 60s work in which he updated scenes from classical art with contemporary figures and settings.
John Levee was an American abstract expressionist painter who had worked in Paris since the year of 1949. He died in 2017.
Caspian is an artist working with text, color and light, guards his identity much like a street/urban artist; hiding camouflaged behind messages of poetic & biographical reflections.
Dganit Blechner’s works have earned her a worldwide reputation earned by her vivid, bright and cheerful pallets of colors along with extraordinary compositions.
Édgar Negret (October 11, 1920 – October 11, 2012) was a modern Latin American abstract sculptor.
Jose Dávila reflects on the failure of utopian, modernist architectural principles in his assemblages, mixed-media works, photography and installations.
Roberto Marx was a Brazilian landscape architect as well as a painter, printmaker, ecologist, naturalist, and musician, successful in all these fields.
Antonio Dias was a Brazilian artist born in 1944. His work was influenced by several artistic movements, including Pop Art and Minimalism.
Arnaldo Roche Rabell was a celebrated Puerto Rican artist whose revolutionary imagery played a pivotal role in the development of his nation's art scene.
Carlos Irizarry is a Puerto Rican painter and engraver who became famous for making politically loaded works of art that were underlined by a strong national temperament.
Pierre Jeanneret was a Swiss architect who designed some of the most famous buildings of the 20th century with his cousin, Le Corbusier.
Jarbas Lopes is a Brazilian artist born in 1964, in Nova Iguacu. His work was included in numerous solo and group exhibitions.
Burt Glinn was an American photographer who worked with Magnum Photos. He photographed people such as Andy Warhol and Helen Frankenthaler.
Wolfgang Stiller is a German artist born in 1961 in Wiesbaden. He has exhibited extensively both nationally and internationally.
Richard Sheridan Franklin Bowling OBE RA LG, better known as Frank Bowling, is a British artist born in Bartica, Guyana.
Scooter LaForge is an American artist whose work can be characterized as Pop Art partnered with abstract expressionism and Dutch classicism.
Hossein Edalatkhah is an Iranian artist born in 1979. He combines social, political, historical, sexual, and religious themes in his works.
Mareo Rodríguez is a Mexican architect and visual artist whose work is a look at the matter, topography, and natural territory conceived as a living being.
Gordon House was a British artist and designer who was born in Pontardawe, Glamorgan, in 1932. His work was included in various exhibitions.
Bernard Cathelin was a French artist who was born in 1919. He was a member of the School of Paris which included Matisse, De Buffet and Brianchon.
Jane Puylagarde is a French artist who was born in 1958, in Paris. Her work has been regularly exhibited in Parisian and international galleries.

Rivane Neuenschwander is a well known Brazilian conceptual artists whose work explores language, nature, the passing of time and social interactions.

Martin Barooshian is an American master painter and printmaker who was born in 1929. His work was included in various exhibitions.
Andrew Davis is a contemporary artist who lives and works in Staunton, VA. He is known for his colorful, vibrant paintings.
Vladimir Kraynyk is a contemporary artist based in Winnipeg, Canada. His work has been included in various exhibitions.
Alvaro Barrios is a Colombian artist, whose iconic comic book style burgeoned from an early passion for drawing, inspired by the comics he read as a child.

David Choe  is an American figure painter, muralist, graffiti artist and graphic novelist of Korean descent known for his figure paintings.

C215, whose real name is Christian Guémy, is a French street artist known as one of the top stencil artists in the world.
Melbourne natives Dabs and Myla are a dynamic duo who have been living in Los Angeles since 2009 making its streets and walls more beautiful.

Fernando Carlo, known as Cope2, is an American artist who has gained international credit for his work - throw-ups and also a wildstyle graffiti.

The artist Beejoir is best known for his dry-humored and politically focused street art. He works in a broad variety of media experimenting with painting, printmaking, sculpture, photography and stencil.
AJ Fosik is an American artist, born in Detroit, Michigan. He is best known for his carefully crafted and vividly colored wooden sculptures.

Alexone Dizac is a French artist, painter and illustrator, coming from the Graffiti world. He is best known for mixing paint drips, ghost tags drawn with a marker pen or a spray can, flames, one-line geometrical patterns, funny punchlines...

Bezt is a Polish graffiti artist who’s part of artistic duo Etam Cru and is known for quite colorful and sophisticated style expressed through several media.
Parker Ito is an American artist known for his innovative, provocative and almost Dadaistic multimedia and Internet works, sometimes created by his assistants.
Oscar Murillo is a Colombian-British contemporary artist best known for his fast rise in the art world and often called the 21st-century Basquiat.

Claudia Walde, known better by her artistic pseudonym MadC, is a graffiti artist from Germany famous for her large-scale outdoor mural works.
Martin Wong was born in Portland, Ore., in 1946 and grew up in San Francisco, where his parents worked for Standard Oil and the Bechtel Corporation. He received a degree in cerami

Sr. X was born at the beginning of the 80’s in a small town in the north of Spain. After following several Arts degrees, he started to bring his ideas to the street trying to get city people to stop, think or just smile for a moment when they saw his
Jean-Baptiste Bernadet is a French contemporary artist, whose paintings are reminiscent of various styles, minimalist, monochromatic, gestural, impressionistic.
Gregory Siff is an American artist whose work blurs the boundaries between Pop Art and Abstract-expressionism, with a little bit of street art.
ALO is a London-based Italian street artist, best known for his middle-size, highly detailed portraits. He describes his style as Urban Expressionism.
Liu Bolin, born in 1973, is a Chinese contemporary artist who creates amazing works that fuse Performance Art, photography, and protest.

Katrin Fridriks is an Icelandic conceptual artist, the vanguard of a new abstract expressionism movement.
Pejac is a Spanish artist who creates street art and paintings that combine elements of surrealism and fantasy with the artist’s minimalist style.
Tom Sachs is an American contemporary artist and sculptor best known for his elaborate recreations of various Modern icons, all of them masterpieces of engineering and design of one kind or another.
David Ostrowski is a German abstract painter whose monumental works represents the minimalistic simplicity of expression.
My Dog Sighs style is characterised by the combination of melancholic and often naive portraiture with the use of found materials
Cindy Sherman is a photographer who incorporates aspects of feminism, performance art, cultural criticism, and the identity politics into her provocative works.
David LaChapelle is known internationally for his exceptional talent in combining a unique hyper-realistic aesthetic with profound social messages.
Helmut Newton was an influential German fashion photographer famous for his radiant and provocative images of elegant, powerful and sensual women
Mark Ryden is the most important painter of the Lowbrow art movement (Pop Surrealism) and a combiner of pleasing aesthetics with disturbing content.
Joram Roukes is a Dutch fine artist, best known for his large oil paintings where he is blending various stylistic elements.

Pakpoom Silaphan is a Thai artist who explores the phenomena surrounding a "West­Obsessed" world.  Silaphan, influenced by Pop Art of the 20th century, re­works found objects to create his own fresh interpretation of Pop Art.

Bambi is a British street artist whose work is described as rough and masculine in appearance although she explores themes of feminism and popular culture.

Spanish muralist and street artist Escif uses subdued colors and simple lines to communicate his humorous and often direct commentary on capitalism, politics, the economy and other sensitive social issues.

Peter Phillips is a British Pop Artists whose work ranges from oils on canvas to multi-media compositions and collages. Vibrant in color and filled with iconography of images from daily life, Peter’s work appeals to the spectator’s mind.
American artist Richard Avedon was best known for his mixture of portraiture and fashion photography that blurred the line between the two genres.

Georg Baselitz is a  German artist who emerged as a pioneer of German Neo-Expressionist painting style, but from a European perspective, it is more seen as postmodern.

Antony Gormley is a British sculptor who attempts to treat the body not as an object but a place and in making works that enclose the space of a particular body to identify a condition common to all human beings.
Thomas Schütte is a German sculptor and draughtsman, one of the most influential contemporary artists. He lives and works in Germany.
Yue Minjun  is a contemporary Chinese artist best known for his pictorial and sculptural depictions of himself in various settings, usually frozen in hysterical laughter.
Tony Cragg, born in Liverpool is one the foremost world's sculptors. His work questions the limits between man and material world in the most ingenious ways.

Hurvin Anderson is a British painter, born in 1965 in Birmingham, United Kingdom. He is known for his series of paintings titled Peter’s.

Adam McEwen is a British artist whose installations and sculptures are manipulating familiar items, re-purposing them in new, unexpected contexts. His interventions are lowering audience’s indifference to the mass media exposure present in the daily life.

Jordan Nickel aka POSE is Chicago-based artist known for his progressive letter style, technical precision, dedication, and legal troubles that made him a front runner of Chicago’s golden age of graffiti.

Known for his bright colored paintings and drawings, Eddie Martinez is an American artist whose work reflects the urban chaos from the world he lives in.

Nanda Vigo was an Italian artist born in 1936. She is considered a pioneer in modern Italian art.

Andres Serrano is an American visual artist and photographer born in 1950, whose work has been labeled from blasphemous to beautiful. He became notorious through his photos of corpses and his use of feces and bodily fluids.
American photographer Alex Prager has captured the public's eye with her film-like photographs inspired by the visual aesthetics of old Hollywood movies.
Adrian Ghenie is a Romanian painter known for his disturbing portrayals of the eminent figures such as Charles Darwin and Van Gogh.

Felix Gonzalez-Torres was an American artist, of Cuban origin, known for his minimalism inspired installations and sculptures.
James Rizzi was an American Pop artist who was famous for his 3D artwork and his ability to make his viewers happy simply by watching his pieces.

Franz West was an Austrian sculptor and installation artist, born in Vienna in 1947. His sculptures are typically made out of plaster, paper mache, and aluminum, displaying the power of the object and the seriousness of the absurd.
Neo-Dadaist, conceptual and appropriation artist Elaine Sturtevant was best known for her  repetitions of other artists' works that prefigured appropriation.
Canadian born multi-disciplinary artist Marcel Dzama is a draughtsman, painter, and filmmaker best known for his fantastical pen-and-ink figure drawings.
Rineke Dijkstra is Dutch photographer and video artist born in 1959, in Sittard, the Netherlands. She creates close contact with subjects, emphasizing their emotions.
Michael Manning is an American comic book artist born in 1963 in Flushing in the New York City borough of Queens. He is best known for his graphic novel series, The Spider Garden and Tranceptor.

Pipilotti Rist is a Swiss artist who works with video, film, and moving images which are often displayed as projections. She is a pioneer of moving-image art.
Mr. is a Japanese contemporary artist born in 1969, who works in a wide range of media, including painting, sculpture and video. His works are all closely related in aesthetics, style, and theme.

Billy Childish is a prolific British artist, punk rocker, poet and novelist born in 1959, considered as one of the most unconventional and rebellious visionaries.
David Reed is an American abstract artist, mostly known for his large-scale colorful paintings. He is an exhibition curator, colorist, and free thinker.
Richard Pettibone is one of the pioneers of appropriation art. The artist helped set the stage for 80's appropriation art by recycling the pop culture appropriations of Pop Art.
Riusuke Fukahori is a Japanese artist best known for his three-dimensional goldfish paintings created by pouring resin that have an incredible optical illusion effect.
The London Police is an art collaboration between Chaz Barrisson and Bob Gibson that started in 1998 when the artists visited Amsterdam.
Daniel Götesson aka Ekta is a Swedish contemporary artist born in 1978.
Carlos Estévez is one of the most prominent Cuban artists of his generation. He is known as a painter, sculptor and a photographer.
Roberto Fabelo is a widely known Cuban painter, illustrator and sculptor, and one of the most respected premier contemporary artists from Cuba.
Tomás Sánchez is a renowned Cuban artist, best known for his extraordinarily detailed landscapes and paintings of majestic landfills.

Carlos Garaicoa is one of the internationally best known and most influential Cuban artists, whose work has achieved canonical status in his homeland.

Jonathan Monk is a British Contemporary artist who was born in Leicester in 1969. In his practice he replays, recasts and re-examines seminal works of Conceptual and Minimal art by variously witty, ingenious and irreverent means.
Born in 1966, in Dalian, China, Yang Maoyuan is a highly regarded artist well known for his large and diverse body of work encompassing painting, sculpture, photography and installation.
Mantis is a South African born artist who has been a steady contributor to the urban and contemporary art scene for the last ten years.
Gregory Crewdson is an notable American photographer known for striking and surreal imagery of American suburb homes and neighborhoods.
Leonora Carrington was a British painter and author who lived in Mexico City, best known as one of the leading female figures of the Surrealist movement.

Daido Moriyama is a prolific Japanese artist, well-known as a photographer, graphic designer, and writer.  His photographs epitomize wabi-sabi, the Japanese aesthetic of finding beauty in imperfection.

Jan Kaláb aka Cakes aka Point belongs to the oldest active generation of graffiti writers in the Czech Republic.

Nicola López, born in 1975, is an American artist who works in installation, drawing, and printmaking.
Massimo Agostinelli is an emerging American-Italian contemporary artist born in 1987 in London, UK.
Andrea Medjesi-Jones is a British artist, whose paintings and drawings are focused on the nature of image in relation to material process of its making.
Ansel Adams was an iconic American photographer, well-known for his monumental black and white images of national parks and landscapes.
Hans Burkhardt was a Swiss-born American painter, whom many art historians consider one of the greatest abstract expressionists of our time.
